20:- **[P1] Shallow payload validation can still crash rendering** (lines 24, 86) - Rows are filtered only by truthy `id`, but `item.name` is rendered directly. If the API returns an object or array in `name`, React will throw during render. Suggested fix: normalize rows before `setItems`, requiring a primitive `id` and string or null `name`.
